{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775896059357,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba75dc1001qXW0jNyxVWobd7","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ba74b0f001KECtEPDesoBFJF","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":18769,"input":3471,"output":259,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15039}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775896062815,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba76b5c001hZJnUCmZ13kMJ2","messageID":"msg_d7ba75df4001OwzLfzFstNArb9","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896064813,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba76f86001xY5Xr3ZDI31n3M","messageID":"msg_d7ba75df4001OwzLfzFstNArb9","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b7cc8f77c8104a438e96fcb64eadfbdc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: Python SDK/CLI Testing (AR-040)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Develop a comprehensive test suite for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), ensuring reliable coverage of the Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime client libraries. The tests will validate HTTP client contracts, session lifecycle management, file operations, code execution paths, error handling, and timeout behaviors across both control plane and data plane components.\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### Test Modules\n10: \n11: **Unit Tests** (`tests/unit/`):\n12: - HTTP client contract validation (control plane and data plane)\n13: - Configuration resolution (environment variables, token file handling)\n14: - Session header management\n15: - Timeout parameter validation\n16: - Exception hierarchy and error raising\n17: - Utility functions (`create_session`, `read_token_from_file`, `get_logger`)\n18: - URL construction and path joining logic\n19: \n20: **Integration Tests** (`tests/integration/`):\n21: - `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle (create → use → stop)\n22: - `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle (bootstrap → invoke → close)\n23: - Context manager cleanup with and without exceptions\n24: - Data plane initialization after session creation\n25: - Router URL requirement validation\n26: \n27: **Functional Tests** (`tests/functional/`):\n28: - Code execution: `execute_command`, `run_code` for Python code path\n29: - File operations: `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`\n30: - Command failure and `CommandExecutionError` raising\n31: - Session ID bootstrap for Agent Runtime\n32: - Multi-session scenarios\n33: \n34: **Edge Case Tests** (`tests/edge_cases/`):\n35: - Non-zero exit codes in command responses\n36: - Missing response headers (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n37: - 404 handling in `delete_session`\n38: - Timeout buffer logic for `execute_command` (read timeout + 2.0s)\n39: - Base64 encoding/decoding in file writes\n40: - Multipart upload headers\n41: \n42: ### Test Coverage Targets\n43: \n44: | Component | Target Coverage |\n45: |-----------|-----------------|\n46: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | ≥85% |\n47: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | ≥85% |\n48: | `ControlPlaneClient` | ≥80% |\n49: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | ≥85% |\n50: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | ≥80% |\n51: | Utilities (`http.py`, `utils.py`, `log.py`) | ≥90% |\n52: | Exceptions | 100% |\n53: \n54: ### Testing Framework\n55: \n56: - **Test Runner**: `pytest` with async support (if needed)\n57: - **Mocking**: `pytest-mock` / `unittest.mock` for HTTP requests\n58: - **HTTP Mocking**: `responses` or `httpx-mock` for simulating Router and Workload Manager responses\n59: - **Assertions**: `pytest` assertions + custom helpers for JSON validation\n60: - **Fixtures**: Shared fixtures for client instances, session IDs, mock responses\n61: \n62: ### Test Data\n63: \n64: - Sample code snippets (Python, shell commands)\n65: - Test files (text, binary)\n66: - Mock response payloads matching Router/Workload Manager contracts\n67: - Invalid inputs for negative testing\n68: \n69: ## Impact Analysis\n70: \n71: ### Positive Impacts\n72: \n73: 1. **Reliability**: Comprehensive test coverage will catch regressions early, ensuring SDK stability across releases\n74: 2. **Confidence**: Users can trust the SDK for production workloads with validated error handling and timeout behavior\n75: 3. **Maintainability**: Test documentation serves as living specification, aiding onboarding and code reviews\n76: 4. **Debugging**: Clear failure messages and structured test outputs reduce time-to-resolution\n77: 5. **CI/CD Integration**: Automated test suite enables continuous validation on pull requests and releases\n78: \n79: ### Negative Impacts\n80: \n81: 1. **Development Overhead**: Initial test suite development requires significant effort (estimated 40-60 hours for full coverage)\n82: 2. **Maintenance Cost**: Tests must be kept in sync with SDK changes, adding review burden\n83: 3. **Mock Complexity**: HTTP mocking infrastructure may become brittle if API contracts evolve\n84: 4. **Test Execution Time**: Full test suite may take 2-5 minutes, impacting CI pipeline duration\n85: \n86: ### Risk Mitigation\n87: \n88: - Use mock libraries with clear deprecation policies (e.g., `responses`)\n89: - Design tests to be modular and focused on single responsibilities\n90: - Separate unit tests (fast) from integration tests (slower) with pytest markers\n91: - Document test conventions in a `CONTRIBUTING.md` or `tests/README.md`\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Manual Testing Only\n96: \n97: **Approach**: Rely on ad-hoc manual testing through example scripts and end-to-end scenarios.\n98: \n99: **Pros**:\n100: - Zero upfront development cost\n101: - Flexible for exploratory testing\n102: \n103: **Cons**:\n104: - No regression protection\n105: - Not reproducible\n106: - Time-consuming to repeat\n107: - Doesn't cover edge cases systematically\n108: \n109: **Decision**: Rejected. Manual testing alone is insufficient for a production SDK.\n110: \n111: ### Alternative 2: Contract Testing (e.g., Pact)\n112: \n113: **Approach**: Use consumer-driven contract testing to validate SDK against actual Router/Workload Manager endpoints.\n114: \n115: **Pros**:\n116: - Validates real API contracts\n117: - Catches API drift early\n118: - Provider-side feedback loop\n119: \n120: **Cons**:\n121: - Requires provider-side mock server setup\n122: - Overkill for current scope (Router/WM contracts are stable)\n123: - Additional infrastructure complexity\n124: \n125: **Decision**: Deferred. Contract testing can be added later if Router/Workload Manager APIs become more dynamic or if provider teams adopt Pact.\n126: \n127: ### Alternative 3: Property-Based Testing (e.g., Hypothesis)\n128: \n129: **Approach**: Use property-based testing to generate random inputs and validate invariants (e.g., \"session ID is always present after successful creation\").\n130: \n131: **Pros**:\n132: - Finds edge cases through fuzzing\n133: - Concise test definitions for invariants\n134: \n135: **Cons**:\n136: - Learning curve for team\n137: - May produce flaky tests if invariants are ill-defined\n138: - Still requires mocking infrastructure\n139: \n140: **Decision**: Optional. Can be added for specific invariants (e.g., timeout logic) after basic test coverage is established.\n141: \n142: ### Alternative 4: Skip Testing for CLI\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Focus tests only on SDK client classes; exclude CLI scripts from automated testing.\n145: \n146: **Pros**:\n147: - Reduces scope\n148: - CLI is often simpler than SDK\n149: \n150: **Cons**:\n151: - CLI is user-facing and critical for quickstart experience\n152: - CLI bugs may block adoption\n153: - CLI scripts often duplicate SDK logic\n154: \n155: **Decision**: Include CLI tests. CLI scripts (`scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, example scripts) should be tested with subprocess mocking or integration testing.\n156: \n157: ## Implementation Plan\n158: \n159: ### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1)\n160: - Set up pytest project structure\n161: - Create fixtures for mock HTTP responses\n162: - Implement utility tests (`http.py`, `utils.py`, `log.py`)\n163: - Define test conventions and markers\n164: \n165: ### Phase 2: Control Plane Tests (Week 2)\n166: - Unit tests for `ControlPlaneClient`\n167: - Session creation/deletion scenarios\n168: - Auth token resolution\n169: - Error handling (404, network failures)\n170: \n171: ### Phase 3: Code Interpreter Data Plane Tests (Week 3)\n172: - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` tests\n173: - Execute command, run code, files API\n174: - Timeout logic validation\n175: - Context manager cleanup\n176: \n177: ### Phase 4: Agent Runtime Tests (Week 4)\n178: - `AgentRuntimeClient` tests\n179: - Session ID bootstrap\n180: - Invoke scenarios\n181: - Error handling\n182: \n183: ### Phase 5: Integration & Edge Cases (Week 5)\n184: - End-to-end client workflows\n185: - Edge cases and negative testing\n186: - CLI script tests\n187: - Coverage verification\n188: \n189: ### Phase 6: CI Integration & Documentation (Week 6)\n190: - GitHub Actions workflow configuration\n191: - Test reporting and coverage badges\n192: - Documentation updates\n193: - Handoff review\n194: \n195: ## Success Criteria\n196: \n197: 1. All test modules pass with ≥85% coverage for main client classes\n198: 2. Test suite executes in <5 minutes on CI\n199: 3. No flaky tests across 20 consecutive runs\n200: 4. Pull request template includes test requirement checklist\n201: 5. Test failures produce clear, actionable error messages\n202: 6. New SDK features cannot be merged without corresponding tests\n203: \n204: ## Resources Required\n205: \n206: - **Engineering**: 1 senior Python developer, 40-60 hours total\n207: - **Reviewers**: SDK maintainers for test design review\n208: - **Infrastructure**: GitHub Actions CI (already available)\n209: - **Dependencies**: pytest, pytest-mock, responses, pytest-cov (added to `pyproject.toml` dev deps)\n210: \n211: ## Open Questions\n212: \n213: 1. Should tests require actual Router/Workload Manager deployments for subset of integration tests, or rely entirely on mocking? (Current plan: full mocking for reproducibility; optional smoke tests with real services)\n214: 2. How should tests handle Kubernetes service account token file (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`) in CI environments? (Current plan: mock `read_token_from_file` to return empty string or test token)\n215: 3. Should CLI tests be classified as integration tests (require subprocess spawning) or unit tests (mock subprocess)? (Current plan: subprocess mocking for unit tests; optional integration tests for example scripts)\n216: \n217: ## Approval\n218: \n219: - [ ] SDK Lead\n220: - [ ] Engineering Manager\n221: - [ ] QA/Testing Representative\n\n(End of file - total 221 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: Python SDK/CLI Testing (AR-040)\n\n## Purpose\n\nDevelop a comprehensive test suite for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`), ensuring reliable coverage of the Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime client libraries. The tests will validate HTTP client contracts, session lifecycle management, file operations, code execution paths, error handling, and timeout behaviors across both control plane and data plane components.\n\n## Scope\n\n### Test Modules\n\n**Unit Tests** (`tests/unit/`):\n- HTTP client contract validation (control plane and data plane)\n- Configuration resolution (environment variables, token file handling)\n- Session header management\n- Timeout parameter validation\n- Exception hierarchy and error raising\n- Utility functions (`create_session`, `read_token_from_file`, `get_logger`)\n- URL construction and path joining logic\n\n**Integration Tests** (`tests/integration/`):","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775896064797,"end":1775896064811}}}}
