{"type":"text","timestamp":1775896188113,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba838f1001GeEdFV8GVt3PGq","messageID":"msg_d7ba824b8001c40rfzEEGGs6Ua","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write a comprehensive proposal.md for AR-041 E2E Integration Testing:","time":{"start":1775896188111,"end":1775896188111}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896188254,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba954d2001vCKn6xMumzOUNc","messageID":"msg_d7ba824b8001c40rfzEEGGs6Ua","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-767c395cb4cb4120915e21459af777c8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: E2E Integration Testing (AR-041)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis proposal outlines the implementation of comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration testing for the AgentCube platform, focusing on validating the complete system lifecycle from CRD creation through client-go interactions, controller operations, and component interactions.\n\n## Purpose\n\nDevelop a robust E2E test suite that validates the AgentCube platform's behavior in a real Kubernetes environment, ensuring that all components (Workload Manager, Router, Controller Manager, Picod, Agentd) integrate correctly with the generated client-go library and that the system meets its functional and non-functional requirements.\n\n## Module\n\n`test/e2e`\n\n## Language\n\nGo\n\n## Size\n\nL\n\n## Scope\n\n### Test Infrastructure\n\n**Framework Setup** (`test/e2e/framework/`):\n- Kubernetes test environment using envtest or Kind\n- Test framework utilities (namespace management, resource cleanup, assertions)\n- Client-go clientset initialization and configuration\n- Shared fixtures and test helpers\n- Logging and test result collection\n\n**Makefile Integration**:\n- `make e2e` target for running E2E tests\n- `make e2e-clean` target for test environment cleanup\n- Integration with existing CI/CD pipeline (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`)\n\n### Client-Go Integration Tests\n\n**CRD Lifecycle Tests** (`test/e2e/crd/`):\n- AgentRuntime creation, retrieval, update, deletion\n- CodeInterpreter creation, retrieval, update, deletion\n- Default value validation (maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout)\n- Status subresource operations\n- List and Watch operations with label selectors\n- Patch operations (strategic merge, JSON merge)\n- Conflict detection and handling (resource version checks)\n\n**Typed Client Tests** (`test/e2e/client/`):\n- `AgentRuntimeInterface` CRUD operations\n- `CodeInterpreterInterface` CRUD operations\n- Namespace-scoped operations\n- Field validation and error handling\n- Retry logic for transient failures\n- Timeouts and context cancellation\n\n**Informer Tests** (`test/e2e/informer/`):\n- SharedInformerFactory initialization\n- AgentRuntimeInformer event handlers (add, update, delete)\n- CodeInterpreterInformer event handlers\n- Cache synchronization and WaitForCacheSync\n- Lister operations (list, get by namespace)\n- Informer restart and recovery\n\n### Controller Integration Tests\n\n**Workload Manager Tests** (`test/e2e/workloadmanager/`):\n- Sandbox pod creation from AgentRuntime spec\n- Pod template application and customization\n- Session ID generation and management\n- Pod lifecycle management (creation, deletion, status updates)\n- Session timeout and idle cleanup\n- Error handling (invalid pod templates, missing fields)\n- Concurrency handling (multiple AgentRuntime creations)\n\n**Router Tests** (`test/e2e/router/`):\n- Session routing to backend services\n- Redis session management (create, read, delete)\n- Authentication and authorization (Bearer token validation)\n- Load balancing across multiple instances\n- Session expiration handling\n- Health check and readiness probe routing\n\n**Controller Manager Tests** (`test/e2e/controllermanager/`):\n- CRD reconciliation and status updates\n- Condition management (Ready, Progressing, Failed)\n- Event recording and annotation\n- Finalizer handling and cleanup\n- Multiple controller coordination\n\n### Component Interaction Tests\n\n**End-to-End Workflows** (`test/e2e/workflows/`):\n- Complete AgentRuntime lifecycle (create → reconcile → session → cleanup)\n- Complete CodeInterpreter lifecycle (create → reconcile → session → cleanup)\n- Cross-namespace resource interactions\n- Multi-tenant isolation validation\n- Rolling updates and version transitions\n\n**Python SDK Integration** (`test/e2e/sdk/`):\n- Python SDK against live AgentCube deployment\n- ControlPlaneClient session management\n- CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient operations\n- AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient operations\n- Error propagation and exception handling\n\n**CLI Integration** (`test/e2e/cli/`):\n- CLI commands against live cluster\n- Runtime build, pack, publish, invoke operations\n- Configuration validation\n- Error reporting and user feedback\n\n### Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| Client-go generated code | ≥80% |\n| CRD validation | 100% |\n| Controller reconciliation | ≥75% |\n| Router routing logic | ≥80% |\n| Python SDK (integration) | ≥70% |\n| CLI (integration) | ≥70% |\n\n### Test Categories\n\n**Smoke Tests** (fast, critical path):\n- CRD creation and deletion\n- Basic client-go operations\n- Controller startup and health checks\n\n**Integration Tests** (medium speed):\n- Component interactions\n- Controller reconciliation\n- Router session management\n\n**Full E2E Tests** (slow, complete workflows):\n- End-to-end user workflows\n- Multi-component scenarios\n- Performance and stress testing\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Positive Impacts\n\n1. **Quality Assurance**: Comprehensive E2E tests catch integration issues that unit tests miss, ensuring system reliability\n2. **Regression Prevention**: Automated test suite prevents regressions when adding new features or refactoring\n3. **Confidence in Releases**: Validated behavior across real Kubernetes environments increases release confidence\n4. **Documentation**: Test cases serve as living documentation of system behavior and API contracts\n5. **Faster Development**: Quick feedback loop enables faster iterations and debugging\n6. **CI/CD Integration**: Automated testing in pull requests ensures code quality before merge\n\n### Negative Impacts\n\n1. **Development Overhead**: Initial test suite development requires significant effort (estimated 80-120 hours)\n2. **Maintenance Cost**: Tests must be kept in sync with API changes and feature additions\n3. **Test Execution Time**: Full E2E suite may take 10-15 minutes, impacting CI pipeline duration\n4. **Infrastructure Requirements**: Requires Kind or real Kubernetes cluster for execution\n5. **Test Flakiness**: Integration tests may be flaky due to timing issues and external dependencies\n\n### Risk Mitigation\n\n- Use envtest for faster unit-style integration tests, Kind for full E2E\n- Implement proper test isolation and cleanup to avoid test interference\n- Use test markers to categorize tests (smoke, integration, e2e) for selective execution\n- Implement retry logic and proper timeouts for transient failures\n- Use fixtures and shared utilities to reduce code duplication\n- Document test conventions and best practices in `test/e2e/README.md`\n- Regularly review and refactor test code to maintain quality\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Manual Testing Only\n\n**Approach**: Rely on manual testing through example scripts and ad-hoc validation.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Zero upfront development cost\n- Flexible for exploratory testing\n- No test maintenance overhead\n\n**Cons**:\n- No regression protection\n- Not reproducible\n- Time-consuming to repeat\n- Doesn't cover edge cases systematically\n- Error-prone for complex workflows\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Manual testing alone is insufficient for a production platform with multiple components.\n\n### Alternative 2: Unit Tests Only\n\n**Approach**: Focus exclusively on unit tests, mocking all external dependencies.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Fast execution\n- Easy to set up\n- No infrastructure requirements\n\n**Cons**:\n- Doesn't validate real Kubernetes interactions\n- Mocks may not reflect real behavior\n- Missing integration issues\n- No confidence in multi-component workflows\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Unit tests are necessary but insufficient for validating system-wide behavior.\n\n### Alternative 3: Contract Testing (e.g., Pact)\n\n**Approach**: Use consumer-driven contract testing to validate client-go against actual Kubernetes API server contracts.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Validates real API contracts\n- Catches API drift early\n- Provider-side feedback loop\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires provider-side mock server setup\n- Overkill for Kubernetes client-go (API is stable)\n- Additional infrastructure complexity\n- Doesn't test controller logic or component interactions\n\n**Decision**: Deferred. Contract testing can be added later if custom API contracts become more complex.\n\n### Alternative 4: Property-Based Testing (e.g., GopherCheck)\n\n**Approach**: Use property-based testing to generate random inputs and validate invariants.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Finds edge cases through fuzzing\n- Concise test definitions for invariants\n- Good for data validation\n\n**Cons**:\n- Learning curve for team\n- May produce flaky tests if invariants are ill-defined\n- Doesn't replace scenario-based E2E tests\n- Still requires infrastructure setup\n\n**Decision**: Optional. Can be added for specific invariants (e.g., CRD validation) after basic E2E coverage is established.\n\n### Alternative 5: External Test Framework (e.g., kuttl)\n\n**Approach**: Use a Kubernetes-specific test framework like kuttl for declarative E2E tests.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Kubernetes-native\n- Declarative test definitions\n- Built-in assertion and cleanup\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional dependency\n- Learning curve\n- Less flexible for custom test logic\n- May not integrate well with existing Go test ecosystem\n\n**Decision**: Considered. kuttl could be used for CRD-specific tests, but custom Go test framework provides more flexibility for controller and component testing.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Set up test infrastructure and framework\n- Configure Kind/envtest environment\n- Implement basic test utilities\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Create `test/e2e/framework/` directory structure\n- Implement test framework (namespace management, client initialization)\n- Set up Makefile targets (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`)\n- Create `test/e2e/conftest.go` with test fixtures\n- Implement logging and test result collection\n- Write documentation (`test/e2e/README.md`)\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Working test framework\n- Basic smoke test (cluster creation, CRD installation)\n- CI/CD integration\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- `make e2e` runs without errors\n- Kind cluster creates and destroys successfully\n- Basic test passes in CI environment\n\n### Phase 2: Client-Go Tests (Week 2)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate generated client-go code\n- Test CRD lifecycle operations\n- Verify informer functionality\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement `test/e2e/crd/` tests (CRUD operations, defaults, validation)\n- Implement `test/e2e/client/` tests (typed client operations)\n- Implement `test/e2e/informer/` tests (event handlers, cache sync)\n- Add error handling tests (conflicts, not found, forbidden)\n- Implement list and watch tests with selectors\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Complete client-go test coverage\n- Validation of CRD OpenAPIV3Schema\n- Informer event handling verification\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All client-go tests pass\n- ≥80% code coverage for client-go generated code\n- No flaky tests\n\n### Phase 3: Controller Tests (Week 3)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate controller reconciliation logic\n- Test Workload Manager sandbox creation\n- Verify Controller Manager status updates\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement `test/e2e/workloadmanager/` tests\n- Implement `test/e2e/controllermanager/` tests\n- Test pod template application\n- Test session lifecycle management\n- Add error scenario tests (invalid templates, missing fields)\n- Test concurrency and race conditions\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Controller reconciliation test suite\n- Status update and condition management verification\n- Error handling and recovery tests\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All controller tests pass\n- ≥75% code coverage for controller logic\n- Controllers handle error scenarios correctly\n\n### Phase 4: Router Tests (Week 4)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate routing logic\n- Test session management\n- Verify authentication and authorization\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement `test/e2e/router/` tests\n- Test session routing to backend services\n- Test Redis session management\n- Add authentication tests (Bearer token validation)\n- Test session expiration and cleanup\n- Add load balancing tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Router routing logic test suite\n- Session management verification\n- Authentication and authorization tests\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All router tests pass\n- ≥80% code coverage for router logic\n- Sessions route correctly to backends\n\n### Phase 5: Component Interaction Tests (Week 5)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate end-to-end workflows\n- Test multi-component scenarios\n- Verify cross-namespace isolation\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement `test/e2e/workflows/` tests\n- Test complete AgentRuntime lifecycle\n- Test complete CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n- Add multi-tenant isolation tests\n- Test rolling updates and version transitions\n- Add error propagation tests\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- End-to-end workflow test suite\n- Multi-component scenario tests\n- Cross-namespace isolation verification\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All workflow tests pass\n- End-to-end workflows complete successfully\n- Multi-tenant isolation is enforced\n\n### Phase 6: SDK and CLI Integration (Week 6)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate Python SDK against live deployment\n- Test CLI commands against live cluster\n- Verify error propagation\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement `test/e2e/sdk/` tests\n- Implement `test/e2e/cli/` tests\n- Test Python SDK session management\n- Test CLI runtime operations\n- Add error propagation tests\n- Verify user-facing error messages\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Python SDK integration test suite\n- CLI integration test suite\n- Error propagation verification\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All SDK and CLI tests pass\n- ≥70% code coverage for SDK integration\n- CLI commands work as expected\n\n### Phase 7: Performance and Stress Testing (Week 7)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Validate system performance under load\n- Test scalability limits\n- Identify performance bottlenecks\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Implement performance tests (throughput, latency)\n- Add stress tests (high concurrency, large workloads)\n- Test resource limits and quotas\n- Add resource cleanup verification\n- Profile and identify bottlenecks\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Performance test suite\n- Stress test results\n- Performance benchmarks\n- Optimization recommendations\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- System meets performance requirements\n- No memory leaks or resource exhaustion\n- Graceful degradation under load\n\n### Phase 8: CI/CD Integration and Documentation (Week 8)\n\n**Objectives**:\n- Integrate tests with CI/CD pipeline\n- Document test framework and usage\n- Create test run reports\n\n**Tasks**:\n- Update `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` for all test categories\n- Add test result reporting and coverage badges\n- Create comprehensive documentation\n- Write test contribution guidelines\n- Add troubleshooting guide\n- Create test run templates\n\n**Deliverables**:\n- Fully integrated CI/CD pipeline\n- Complete documentation\n- Test run reports\n- Troubleshooting guide\n\n**Success Criteria**:\n- All tests pass in CI/CD\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n- New contributors can run tests easily\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Organization\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── framework/\n│   ├── framework.go           # Test framework initialization\n│   ├── client.go              # Client-go clientset initialization\n│   ├── namespace.go           # Namespace management\n│   ├── assertions.go          # Custom assertions and helpers\n│   └── fixtures.go            # Shared fixtures and test data\n├── crd/\n│   ├── agentruntime_test.go   # AgentRuntime CRD tests\n│   └── codeinterpreter_test.go # CodeInterpreter CRD tests\n├── client/\n│   ├── agentruntime_client_test.go\n│   └── codeinterpreter_client_test.go\n├── informer/\n│   ├── agentruntime_informer_test.go\n│   └── codeinterpreter_informer_test.go\n├── workloadmanager/\n│   ├── sandbox_creation_test.go\n│   └── session_management_test.go\n├── router/\n│   ├── routing_test.go\n│   └── session_test.go\n├── controllermanager/\n│   ├── reconciliation_test.go\n│   └── status_test.go\n├── workflows/\n│   ├── agentruntime_lifecycle_test.go\n│   └── codeinterpreter_lifecycle_test.go\n├── sdk/\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_test.go\n│   └── agentruntime_test.go\n├── cli/\n│   ├── build_test.go\n│   └── invoke_test.go\n├── performance/\n│   ├── throughput_test.go\n│   └── stress_test.go\n├── conftest.go                # Test suite configuration\n└── README.md                  # Test documentation\n```\n\n### Test Execution\n\n**Local Development**:\n```bash\n# Run all E2E tests\nmake e2e\n\n# Run specific test category\nmake e2e TESTS=crd\n\n# Run with verbose output\nmake e2e TEST_FLAGS=-v\n\n# Clean up test environment\nmake e2e-clean\n```\n\n**CI/CD Pipeline**:\n- Run smoke tests on every pull request\n- Run integration tests on main branch\n- Run full E2E tests before release\n- Collect test results and coverage reports\n\n### Test Markers\n\nUse test markers to categorize tests:\n\n```go\n// +build e2e\n// +build smoke\n// +build integration\n// +build performance\n```\n\nRun specific categories:\n```bash\n# Run smoke tests only\nmake e2e TEST_TAGS=smoke\n\n# Run integration tests only\nmake e2e TEST_TAGS=integration\n```\n\n### Test Data Management\n\n**Fixtures** (`test/e2e/framework/fixtures.go`):\n- Sample AgentRuntime manifests\n- Sample CodeInterpreter manifests\n- Test configurations\n- Mock responses\n\n**Test Secrets**:\n- Use test secrets from `test/e2e/secrets/`\n- Never commit real credentials\n- Rotate test secrets regularly\n\n### Test Isolation\n\nEach test should:\n- Create its own namespace\n- Clean up resources after completion\n- Not depend on other tests\n- Use unique resource names\n- Handle failures gracefully\n\n### Error Handling\n\n**Test Failures**:\n- Log detailed error messages\n- Capture Kubernetes events\n- Save pod logs for failed pods\n- Provide reproduction steps\n\n**Flaky Tests**:\n- Implement retry logic for transient failures\n- Use proper timeouts and poll intervals\n- Identify and fix flaky tests promptly\n- Document known flakiness with TODOs\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. **Test Coverage**: All test categories achieve target coverage (CRD: 100%, controllers: ≥75%, client-go: ≥80%)\n2. **Test Execution**: Full E2E suite completes in <15 minutes on CI\n3. **Test Stability**: No flaky tests across 20 consecutive runs\n4. **CI/CD Integration**: All tests pass in CI/CD pipeline on every pull request\n5. **Documentation**: Complete documentation for test framework, usage, and contribution\n6. **Bug Detection**: E2E tests catch at least 5 integration bugs before release\n7. **Developer Adoption**: New contributors can run and extend tests with <1 hour onboarding\n8. **Performance**: System meets performance requirements under test load\n\n## Resources Required\n\n### Engineering Resources\n\n| Role | Hours | Responsibilities |\n|------|-------|------------------|\n| Senior Go Developer | 80-100 | Test framework, client-go tests, controller tests |\n| Kubernetes Expert | 40-60 | Router tests, component interaction tests |\n| Python Developer | 30-40 | SDK integration tests |\n| QA Engineer | 20-30 | Test strategy, documentation, CI/CD integration |\n| **Total** | **170-230** | |\n\n### Infrastructure\n\n- **Kind Cluster**: Local testing environment\n- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions with Kind integration\n- **Test Registry**: Container registry for test images\n- **Monitoring**: Test result collection and reporting\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Tool | Version | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| Go | 1.23+ | Test implementation |\n| Python | 3.10+ | SDK integration tests |\n| Kind | v0.30.0+ | Local Kubernetes cluster |\n| kubectl | Latest | Cluster operations |\n| Helm | 3.0+ | Chart deployment |\n| pytest | Latest | Python test runner |\n| controller-runtime | Latest | envtest framework |\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. **Test Environment**: Should we use envtest for faster unit-style integration tests, or Kind for full E2E tests only?\n   - **Current Plan**: Use envtest for client-go and controller tests, Kind for full E2E workflows\n\n2. **Test Data**: Should we use real test images or mock images for faster execution?\n   - **Current Plan**: Use lightweight test images (alpine, busybox) for faster execution\n\n3. **Secrets Management**: How should we manage test secrets for authentication?\n   - **Current Plan**: Use test-specific secrets with minimal permissions, rotate regularly\n\n4. **Parallel Execution**: Should tests run in parallel for faster execution?\n   - **Current Plan**: Run tests in parallel where possible, use resource locking for shared resources\n\n5. **Test Retention**: How long should we keep test logs and artifacts?\n   - **Current Plan**: Keep 7 days of logs on failure, 1 day on success\n\n## Approval\n\n- [ ] Tech Lead\n- [ ] Engineering Manager\n- [ ] QA/Testing Representative\n- [ ] Kubernetes Platform Team","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/.github/workflows/e2e.yml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775896188156,"end":1775896188251}}}}
