{"type":"text","timestamp":1775896210663,"sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba979e0001xlu1rC3dV5EFG5","messageID":"msg_d7ba9558e001O4Qxy8XpIZzHBF","sessionID":"ses_28458bfd8ffebRFWZ5Yu42e54k","type":"text","text":"I've written a comprehensive proposal.md for AR-041 E2E Integration Testing. The proposal includes:\n\n**Key Sections:**\n- **Purpose**: Establishes the need for comprehensive E2E testing of the AgentCube platform\n- **Scope**: Detailed breakdown covering test infrastructure, client-go integration, controller tests, router tests, component interactions, and SDK/CLI integration\n- **Impact Analysis**: Covers both positive (quality assurance, regression prevention) and negative (development overhead, maintenance cost) impacts with risk mitigation\n- **Alternatives Considered**: 5 alternatives evaluated (manual testing, unit tests only, contract testing, property-based testing, external frameworks like kuttl)\n- **Implementation Plan**: 8-week phased approach from foundation through CI/CD integration\n- **Testing Strategy**: Test organization, execution, markers, data management, isolation, and error handling\n- **Success Criteria**: 8 measurable criteria including coverage targets, execution time, and stability requirements\n\n**Coverage Targets:**\n- Client-go: ≥80%\n- Controllers: ≥75%\n- Router: ≥80%\n- SDK/CLI integration: ≥70%\n- CRD validation: 100%\n\n**Estimated Effort**: 170-230 engineering hours across 8 weeks with a team of 4-5 engineers.","time":{"start":1775896210659,"end":1775896210659}}}
